{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3559906,"name":"","username":"TheANT","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-17T23:19:21.900Z","cooked":"<p>We are trying to get localization working for our robot. We are using the limelight 3 and <a href="https://github.com/frc3179/2025-Reefscape/tree/TeleopMove" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">here is our code.</a> We have the following problems.</p>
<ol>
<li>We can’t get the auto starting state to have for our swerve drive pose estimator initalization.</li>
<li>Limelight updates the pose only once at the begining (if it can see it) and never again.</li>
<li>Pose 0, 0 is our starting state and not the orgin as we found out by runing a command that moves our robot to the orgin for testing.</li>
</ol>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-17T23:23:25.885Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":21,"reads":295,"readers_count":294,"score":164.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/frc3179/2025-Reefscape/tree/TeleopMove","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"GitHub - frc3179/2025-Reefscape at TeleopMove","clicks":14}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":59968,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3560195,"name":"Jackson Elia","username":"Traptricker","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-18T04:22:31.718Z","cooked":"<p>So I assume <code>TrackingSubsystem</code> is where your pose estimation is happening? You need to make sure you are updating your poseEstimator with your swerve measurements and your limelight measurements somewhere in your code. For example, you could add a new vision measurement (from your limelight) to the pose estimator in the periodic.</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">public void periodic() {
  ...other code...
  // You might want to check if the Pose2d you're getting from your limelight is new
  // Also you might want to try and account for latency with the timestamp
  poseEstimator.addVisionMeasurement(visionMeasurementPose, currentTimeStampSeconds);
}
</code></pre>
<p>As for resetting your pose during auto, you can use <code>resetPosition</code>. We have our pose estimator in our swerve drive, but I’m sure you could figure something out to make it work with your <code>TrackingSubsystem</code>.</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">  /**
   * Resets the estimated pose of the robot. The gyro does not need to be reset as the pose
   * estimator will take care of that.
   *
   * @param pose the new pose to set the robot to
   */
  public void resetEstimatedPose(Pose2d pose) {
    poseEstimator.resetPosition(rawGyroRotation, getModulePositions(), pose);
  }
</code></pre>
<p>At the beginning of your autonomous command, just call this method with the initial pose of the trajectory.</p>
<p>Also, you should be updating your pose estimator with your module positions, probably in your swerve subsystem’s periodic.</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">    poseEstimator.update(rawGyroRotation, modulePositions);
</code></pre>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-18T04:22:31.718Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":273,"readers_count":272,"score":64.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"Jackson Elia","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53032,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4829 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/2","custom_user_title":"4829 Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3560558,"name":"","username":"TheANT","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-18T14:45:42.547Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks for your reply. Would our TeleopTracking.java command set as default not work instead of using the periodic in the <code>TrackingSubsystem</code>.<br>
We did have the reset estimated pose for the pose estimator but we could not get our starting pose of our robot at the start of auto. Our problem is that our autos don’t have a designated starting position so we need to, at runtime, find this pose.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-18T14:45:42.547Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":181,"readers_count":180,"score":46.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":53032,"username":"Traptricker","name":"Jackson Elia","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":59968,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3560668,"name":"Jackson Elia","username":"Traptricker","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-18T15:54:48.306Z","cooked":"<p>Oh, I’m sorry, I didn’t see that command. Yes what you have can definitely work. I think the reason its not working is because you have booleans <code>doRejectUpdate1</code>, <code>doRejectUpdate2</code>, and <code>doRejectUpdate3</code>, but you never set them to false. Initialize them to false and if the heading rate is under 720, set them to false.</p>
<p>What are you doing for autos? If you’re using pathplanner, you can get the initial pose from a trajectory.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-18T15:54:48.306Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":172,"readers_count":171,"score":44.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"Jackson Elia","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":59968,"username":"TheANT","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53032,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4829 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/4","custom_user_title":"4829 Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3560710,"name":"","username":"TheANT","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-18T16:24:57.739Z","cooked":"<p>We are using path planner but not for the starting position. We automatic pathfinding for the first path because of the inconsistant and inaccurate placement of the robot. I know that the placement is close to the correct position but I am looking to run the same auto from multiple different positions in case our alliance members have unique starting positions. To do this we use the PtathPlannerPath and the relative functions in it. The code that does this is not yet on github.</p>","post_number":5,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-18T16:24:57.739Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":4,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":151,"readers_count":150,"score":40.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":53032,"username":"Traptricker","name":"Jackson Elia","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":59968,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/5","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3560736,"name":"Jackson Elia","username":"Traptricker","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-18T16:36:41.177Z","cooked":"<p>If its close enough to the correct position, you could probably just reset it to the path’s initial pose, and then the limelights will correct for it, just really make sure you get the robot heading correct. As for running the same auto from multiple positions, I wouldn’t suggest doing that. Rather make a few different autos for a few different placements. But if you’re dead-set on doing that, you could decide on a few different starting positions and then use a sendable chooser to select the starting position for your auto.</p>","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-18T16:36:41.177Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":132,"readers_count":131,"score":31.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"Jackson Elia","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":59968,"username":"TheANT","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53032,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4829 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/6","custom_user_title":"4829 Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3560747,"name":"","username":"TheANT","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-18T16:48:55.589Z","cooked":"<p>I will look to do that. What would you recomend for the standard deviations for the limelights to correct the position of the robot?</p>","post_number":7,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-18T16:48:55.589Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":6,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":115,"readers_count":114,"score":33.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":53032,"username":"Traptricker","name":"Jackson Elia","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":59968,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/7","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3561129,"name":"Jackson Elia","username":"Traptricker","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-18T21:37:28.229Z","cooked":"<p>Depends on how in depth you want to do it. My team variably changes the standard deviations based on how far away we are from the april tags, but if that sounds like too much work you could easily do something where you only add vision measurements when you’re 2 meters or closer.</p>
<p>This is the lookup table we use, maybe you could use some of those values? We have the rotation std dev really high because we trust our gyro not to drift very much during the match.</p>
<pre data-code-wrap="java"><code class="lang-java">  public static final double[][] ONE_APRIL_TAG_LOOKUP_TABLE = {
    // {distance in meters, x std deviation, y std deviation, r (in degrees) std deviation}
    {0, 0.02, 0.02, Units.degreesToRadians(180000)},
    {1.5, 0.1, 0.1, Units.degreesToRadians(180000)},
    {3, 4.0, 4.0, Units.degreesToRadians(180000)},
    {4.5, 8.0, 6.0, Units.degreesToRadians(180000)},
    {8, 10.5, 10.5, Units.degreesToRadians(180000)}
  };
</code></pre>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-18T21:37:28.229Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":117,"readers_count":116,"score":43.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"Jackson Elia","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":59968,"username":"TheANT","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53032,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4829 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/8","custom_user_title":"4829 Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3561340,"name":"","username":"TheANT","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-19T01:16:24.996Z","cooked":"<p>We got it generally working we just need to trust our gryo less. Thanks for the help we will inplement your reconmendations latter. Can you pease help with this function for the solution. The whole goal of this was to drive to a Pose2d (the sources). here is the functions that should do it and it does not. It does not follow at all or flip.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public static Command endPoseToCommand(Pose2d endPose, double goalEndVelocity, boolean flip) {
            PathConstraints constraints = PathConstraints.unlimitedConstraints(12.0); // You can also use unlimited constraints, only limited by motor torque and nominal battery voltage
            FlippingUtil.fieldSizeX = xMiddleMeters * 2;
            FlippingUtil.fieldSizeY = yMiddleMeters * 2;

            if (flip) {
                return AutoBuilder.pathfindToPose(FlippingUtil.flipFieldPose(endPose), constraints, goalEndVelocity);
            } else {
                return AutoBuilder.pathfindToPose(endPose, constraints, goalEndVelocity);
            }
        }
</code></pre>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-19T01:16:24.996Z","reply_count":2,"reply_to_post_number":8,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":106,"readers_count":105,"score":41.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":53032,"username":"Traptricker","name":"Jackson Elia","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":59968,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/9","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3561347,"name":"","username":"TheANT","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-19T01:20:19.490Z","cooked":"<p>We added the updates to github</p>","post_number":10,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-19T01:20:19.490Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":97,"readers_count":96,"score":19.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":59968,"username":"TheANT","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":59968,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/10","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3562298,"name":"Jackson Elia","username":"Traptricker","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/traptricker/{size}/215403_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-19T20:54:37.328Z","cooked":"<p>What gyro do you use? We use a navx and are pretty confident that it won’t significantly drift during the length of the match. Additionally, if you plan on using Mega tag 2, it might be risky to let your vision measurement affect the estimated heading.</p>
<p>As for <code>endPoseToCommand</code>, are you sure you are correctly configuring AutoBuilder?<br>
<a href="https://pathplanner.dev/pplib-build-an-auto.html#configure-autobuilder" class="onebox" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">https://pathplanner.dev/pplib-build-an-auto.html#configure-autobuilder</a></p>","post_number":11,"post_type":1,"posts_count":19,"updated_at":"2025-03-19T20:54:37.328Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":9,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":89,"readers_count":88,"score":22.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":495973,"topic_slug":"field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following","display_username":"Jackson Elia","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://pathplanner.dev/pplib-build-an-auto.html#configure-autobuilder","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Build an Auto | PathPlanner Docs","clicks":2}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":59968,"username":"TheANT","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":53032,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"4829 Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/field-localization-and-on-the-fly-path-following/495973/11","custom_user_title":"4829 Mentor","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3562544,"name":"","username":"TheANT","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/theant/{size}/197187_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-20T01:56:46.978Z","cooked":"<p>We use the Pidgon 2 after our navX pins got bent and smashed. Our metatag 2 is update close to correct it just can be off on the rotation between 0-45 degrees.</p>
<p>Here is our config in the driveSubsystem for AutoBuilder.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">/** Creates a new DriveSubsystem. */
    public DriveSubsystem() {
      // Load the RobotConfig from the GUI settings. You should probably
      // store this in your Constants file
      RobotConfig config;
      try{
        config = RobotConfig.fromGUISettings();
      } catch (Exception e) {
        // Handle exception as needed
        config = null;
        e.printStackTrace();
      }

      // Configure AutoBuilder last
      AutoBuilder.configure(
              this::getPose, // Robot pose supplier
              this::resetPose, // Method to reset odometry (will be called if your auto has a starting pose)
              this::getRobotRelativeSpeeds, // ChassisSpeeds supplier. MUST BE ROBOT RELATIVE
              this::driveRobotRelative, // Method that will drive the robot given ROBOT RELATIVE ChassisSpeeds. Also optionally outputs individual module feedforwards
              new PPHolonomicDriveController( // PPHolonomicController is the built in path following controller for holonomic drive trains
                      new PIDConstants(30.0, 0.0, 0.0), // Translation PID constants
                      new PIDConstants(20.0, 0.0, 0.0) // Rotation PID constants
              ),
              config, // The robot configuration
